<p>
<seg id="1">Public procurement of construction services and prevention of corruption</seg>
<seg id="2">Joint report by the Supreme Audit Office of the Czech Republic (NKDP) and the Federal Court of Auditors of the Federal Republic of Germany (Brh) on their parallel audits</seg>
<seg id="3">Introduction and overview</seg>
<seg id="4">The award of services by contracting authorities is of great importance both to the State and to the economy.</seg>
<seg id="5">It is the responsibility of the State to use public funds as economically and economically as possible and to ensure fair and regulated competition.</seg>
<seg id="6">In the European Union (EU), the award of services by contracting authorities is an important element in the creation of a single economic area.</seg>
<seg id="7">In order to ensure largely unrestricted competition across borders, contracting authorities are required to comply with EU standards in their procurement operations above certain value limits (thresholds).</seg>
<seg id="8">To this end, EU Member States have to transpose and apply EU procurement law into national law.</seg>
<seg id="9">This has already been done in both the Czech Republic and Germany.</seg>
<seg id="10">Below the EU thresholds, it is left to individual countries to regulate the award of public contracts themselves.</seg>
<seg id="11">The award of services is also an area that is at risk of corruption.</seg>
<seg id="12">In view of the generally high potential for damage, contracting authorities must therefore take appropriate measures to prevent and prevent corruption and unacceptable benefits in the award of their contracts.</seg>
<seg id="13">In January 2011, the Supreme Audit Office of the Czech Republic (NKDP) and the Federal Accounting Court of the Federal Republic of Germany (Brh) agreed to carry out parallel audits on both the EU-wide award.</seg>
<seg id="14">The audits focused on the application of the EU procurement law, which was transposed into national legislation, as well as the prevention of corruption in the award of construction services in building, road and transport infrastructure.</seg>
