<seg id="617">5. Conclusions</seg>
<seg id="618">The cooperation of the two audit offices has proved its worth.</seg>
<seg id="619">• Intra-Community transactions; • risk management at the UST, in particular with regard to the selection of risk-based transactions;</seg>
<seg id="620">The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting UST fraud and in the systems described above.</seg>
<seg id="621">These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.</seg>
<seg id="622">They can also be used to stimulate discussion among interested bodies on the ways in which audit approaches and strategies can be used to combat fraud. This applies to e.g. For example, for relations within and between Member States and the European Commission.</seg>
<seg id="623">The experience and knowledge gained should encourage us to continue to examine the management of the UST together in the future.</seg>
